Italian Red Wine
Nipozzano Chianti Rúfina Riserva 1995
The vineyards of Rufina, in the hills east of Florence, produce some
of the best Chiantis. The Marchese de Frescobaldi family, who
have been at the forefront of Tuscan winemaking since the 1300s,
own the vast Nipozzano estate. The vineyards lie at a relatively
high altitude which can be sensed in the fine bouquet and lingering
elegance of their Riservas. 1995 is an excellent vintage,
showing off its deep ruby colour with intense red fruits on the nose,
well rounded flavours and a firm finish.
NIPOZZANO
FREsCOBALDI
Port
Taylor's Late Bottled Vintage 1992
Taylor's was founded in 1692 and pioneered the LBV
catogorisation of vintage Port. This entails vintage wine spending
five to six years in oak barrels, such that it is ready to drink
upon bottling. The grapes used for the production of this port hail
from the Cima Corgo and Douro Superior areas which are
synonymous for the production of the world finest Port.
The warm and sunny conditions in 1992 produced a excellent
vintage characterised by superb colour and intense fruit highlighted
with plum, blackberry and spicy flavours completed by a
smooth and mellow finish.
TAYLOR'S®
LATE BOTTLED VINTAGE
PORT • 1992
